Name: PST File Format SDK v0.2.0
Description:
Updated version of pstsdk with several bug fixes, including:
* Improved compiler support (several changes, including two patches from hub)
* Fixed Doxygen file to use relative paths (patch from bradhards)
* Fixed bug where {"table::size"} gave incorrect results (bug report from rmsimpson)
* Made {"message::get_subject"} handle empty subjects correctly (bug report from rmsimpson)
* Fixed bug where {"subnode_nonleaf_block"} crashed (bug report from rmsimpson)
* End message iterator for search folders wasn't being created correctly
* Internal bit of a {"block_id"} wasn't being ignored during lookups as required (bug report from xenocloud)

Name: PST File Format SDK v0.1.0
Description: Initial Beta release of the PST File Format SDK.

Name: PST File Format SDK v0.3.0
Description:
Updated version with several bug fixes and a few new features, including:
* Proper handling of a 0 hnid for variable length allocations in tables and property bags
* read_prop didn't work for all types
* Integrated portability work by emk
* New sample application to read images out of a pst file
* Added ability to quickly read the size of variable length props in the PST layer
* Added ability to check to see if a property exists in the PST layer before reading it
* Added the ability to open a folder, search folder, or message directly from a PST object via node_id based on a suggestion and patch by dblok
* Updated MS-PST doc
